About Me

I'm Sakshi Kadu, a Computer Science and Engineering student at YCCE, Nagpur, graduating in 2027. I'm a passionate and curious web developer who believes that clean design, logical structure, and user experience go hand-in-hand.
I started my development journey with simple HTML pages and quickly found myself drawn into the world of interactive, responsive websites. Over time, I’ve built projects using technologies like JavaScript, React, Bootstrap, and GSAP — turning ideas into functional digital products.
Alongside development, I actively enjoy solving problems through Data Structures and Algorithms. To me, code is not just syntax — it’s a way to think, debug, improve, and build smarter.

I’m currently sharpening my skills, working on real-world projects, and constantly learning — because I believe growth doesn’t come from knowing everything, but from never stopping to explore.
